#### 2.0 Literature   

`r emo::ji("four_leaf_clover")` **Read the following papers, and make a `.Rmd` report answering the questions below**:

1. [Paper that you will be comparing Robinson Lab data with](https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/15476286.2021.1963105)  
2. [My mini-review on small non-coding RNAs and their functions in the placenta](https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fgene.2022.868598/full)  
3. [Paper describing the role of microRNAs in the placenta](https://linkinghub-elsevier-com.ezproxy.library.ubc.ca/retrieve/pii/S0002-9378(15)00534-7)  

*Don't hesitate to ask me questions while reading! For example, if you don't understand something, or want to know more.*  

<br>

I don't expect the answers to the below questions to be long, just enough to demonstrate that you understand the functioning of the major biological components of your project.  

Q1. What is the main function of the placenta?  

Q2. Why is studying the placenta important?  

Q3. What are microRNAs?  

Q4. What do we know about microRNAs in the placenta and their contribution to disease?  

Q5. Write a short summary of what the Smith, M.D. et al. paper (Paper 1) discovered.  

Q6. What were some questions you thought might be interesting to find answers to (which haven;t been discussed or researched already), from reading the above papers?  


Download the .Rmd `Literature_Recap_Template.Rmd` template [here](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1JdyU98Ar3j9BUMF8RcwlZ-5liSnOigc9/view?usp=sharing).

