#### 4.0 Make a GitHub Account  

Sign up to [GitHub](https://github.com/). This is where you'll upload all your project code and documents online. Read about what Git and GitHub is [here](https://kinsta.com/knowledgebase/what-is-github/).  

`r emo::ji("space_invader")` See if you can follow this [Intro to Git and GitHub tutorial](https://github.com/BCCHR-trainee-omics-group/StudyGroup/blob/master/workshops/2021-16-02_intro_to_github/TOG_git_tutorial.md) made by the [BCCHR Trainee 'Omics Group (TOG)](https://bcchr.ca/tog) and link your RStudio to your GitHub profile! You can check out [my GitHub](https://github.com/nikita-telkar) to get an idea of how it looks!  

`r emo::ji("four_leaf_clover")` **Let me know your GitHub account, so that I can add you to your project repository**  

***  

#### 5.0 Weekly Log  

`r emo::ji("four_leaf_clover")` **Keep a log of everything that you do - no matter how big or small.**    

We'll discuss it at every weekly meeting that we'll have. This is to give you practice of keeping a record of your work, because even though you might say sometime in the future that "I don't need to write this down, I'll remember!", you definitely will forget (happens to all researchers!)    


